</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236FFFFB7FFFDE2CE286379764FED" blockId="14.[151,1436,1865,1961]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
This species is fairly widespread in the tropical South Pacific (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C4B0EFFB7FFFDE13228637FE54F25" author="Williams" box="[875,1179,1865,1889]" pageId="14" pageNumber="17" refString="Williams, D. J. &amp; Watson, G. W. (1990) The Scale Insects of the Tropical South Pacific Region. Pt. 3. The Soft Scales (Coccidae) and other families. CAB International Institute of Entomology, London. 267 pp." type="book" year="1990">
Williams &amp; Watson, 
<number id="3DC524D8FFB7FFFDE60628637FE54F25" box="[1119,1179,1865,1889]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first confirmed record of this species from 
<collectingCountry id="F31A766FFFB7FFFDE0432847793B4FC1" box="[538,581,1901,1925]" name="Fiji" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fiji</collectingCountry>
. It was quite abundant on the leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D7CFFB7FFFDE1A428477F1B4FC1" box="[1021,1125,1901,1925]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B979EAEDFFB7FFFDE1A428477F1B4FC1" box="[1021,1125,1901,1925]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Bambusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., at the University of the South Pacific, Suva, 
<date id="FFB3103FFFB7FFFDE3D828BB797A4FED" box="[385,516,1937,1961]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2009-07-13">
<number id="3DC524D8FFB7FFFDE3D828BB7AE24FED" box="[385,412,1937,1961]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="13.0">13</number>
.vii. 
<number id="3DC524D8FFB7FFFDE39D28BB797A4FED" box="[452,516,1937,1961]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</date>
.
</paragraph>
